<item>
            <title>[LU-19168] use of uninitialized spinlock in conf-sanity</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19168</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Looks like test 5h and test 26&#160; in conf-sanity that use failloc 0x135 are hitting this warning:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;[ 2152.758458] LustreError: MGC192.168.206.124@tcp: Connection to MGS (at 0@lo) was lost; in progress operations using this service will fail
[ 2152.884525] Lustre: *** cfs_fail_loc=135, val=0***
[ 2152.921897] Lustre: lustre-MDT0000: Not available for connect from 192.168.206.24@tcp (not set up)
[ 2152.986314] BUG: spinlock bad magic on CPU#0, llog_process_th/67005
[ 2152.992460]  lock: 0xffff99fe36363cc0, .magic: 00000000, .owner: &amp;lt;none&amp;gt;/-1, .owner_cpu: 0
[ 2153.000238] CPU: 0 PID: 67005 Comm: llog_process_th Kdump: loaded Tainted: G           O      -------- -  - 4.18.0rh8.10-debug #10
